SIMPLE: inland
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inland
<hw>In"land</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Within the
land; more or less remote from the ocean or from open water; interior;
<as>as, an <ex>inland</ex> town</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧This wide
<xex>inland</xex> sea.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>From <qex>inland</qex> regions to the distant main.</q>
<rj><qau>Cowper.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Limited to the land, or to inland routes; within the
seashore boundary; not passing on, or over, the sea; <as>as,
<ex>inland</ex> transportation, commerce, navigation,
etc.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Confined to a country or state; domestic; not
foreign; <as>as, an <ex>inland</ex> bill of exchange</as>. See
<er>Exchange</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inland</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Inland
<hw>In"land</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The interior part of a
country.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inland</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Inland
<hw>In"land</hw>, <pos>adv.</pos> <def>Into, or towards, the interior,
away from the coast.</def> <rj><au>Cook.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The greatest waves of population have rolled <qex>inland</qex>
from the east.</q> <rj><qau>S. Turner.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inlander</ent>⟦br⟧
